5.1.2 Use Case Deep Dive

Front Office: Client-Facing Agents

The most visible agents in finance are client-facing. By 2026, major banks and wealth managers deploy agents that:

· Answer client queries about account balances, transaction histories, and product features with near-human fluency
· Provide financial advice within regulatory boundaries, recommending products based on client profiles and market conditions
· Execute trades for retail clients, interpreting natural language instructions ("buy $1000 of Apple") and routing orders
· Onboard new clients, guiding them through account opening, identity verification, and initial deposits

