Liability: When agents contribute to clinical decisions, who is liable for errors? The manufacturer? The health system? The clinician? This remains unsettled.

Integration with clinical workflows: Agents that don't fit seamlessly into clinical workflows will not be used. Integration with electronic health records is essential and difficult.

Trust: Patients must trust agents with sensitive health information. Clinicians must trust agents with clinical decisions. Trust is earned slowly and lost quickly.

