6.7 Building a Governance Framework: A Practical Guide

For organizations beginning this journey, here is a practical framework.

6.7.1 Assess Your Current State

· Inventory: What agents do you have deployed? In development? Planned?
· Classify: What risk level does each agent represent? (Consider potential harm, scale, domain)
· Identify gaps: Where are you missing governance? Which agents have no oversight?

6.7.2 Establish Foundations

· Policy: Draft an enterprise AI policy covering agent development, deployment, and monitoring
· Roles: Designate a Chief AI Officer (or equivalent) and establish a governance committee
· Standards: Define technical standards for observability, guardrails, and audit trails

6.7.3 Build for High-Risk Agents First

· Focus governance efforts on agents that could cause significant harm
· For each high-risk agent, conduct a risk assessment, require pre-deployment review, and mandate continuous monitoring
· Document everything

6.7.4 Scale to Medium and Low Risk

· Adapt governance requirements to risk level
· Medium-risk agents may require less rigorous review but still need monitoring
· Low-risk agents may follow streamlined processes

6.7.5 Continuously Improve

· Learn from incidents
· Update policies as technology evolves
· Engage with peers, regulators, and experts
· Invest in governance tools and talent

