6.8 The Future of Governance

As agents become more capable and widespread, governance will evolve.

Technical governance will mature. Today's immature tooling will be replaced by robust platforms for observability, guardrails, and control. Governance will be built into agent infrastructure, not added on.

Regulatory frameworks will converge. The current patchwork of national and sectoral approaches will gradually harmonize, driven by international cooperation and the needs of global business.

Professional roles will emerge. Agent auditor, agent risk manager, agent ethicist—these will become recognized professions with training, certification, and career paths.

Insurance markets will develop. Insurers will offer products for agent-related risks, creating market-based incentives for safety.

Public understanding will grow. As agent interactions become routine, the public will develop intuitions about when to trust agents and when to be wary. This cultural learning is as important as technical governance.

